
// This Hyperlambda code snippet demonstrates how to use the [set-value] slot to modify the value of a node by replacing a specific substring within it. The [strings.replace] slot is used to search for the substring [[clear_button]] within the node referenced by the expression [@.result] and replace it with the string "true". This operation effectively updates the value of the [result] node by substituting the specified substring with the new value.
set-value:x:@.result
   strings.replace:x:@.result
      .:[[clear_button]]
      .:true
